de.elo.ix.client.serverevents

Class IXServerEventsHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.elo.ix.client.serverevents.IXServerEventsHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IXServerEvents, java.rmi.Remote

    public abstract class IXServerEventsHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements IXServerEvents
    This class helps to implement the IXServerEvents interface. Your project should inherit from this class and implement the IXServerEvents methods. Each implmented method has to be added to the collection implementedMethods: implementedMethods["onAfterCheckinSord"] = true; Use the function {ConnectionMap#getConn(IXServerEventsContext) to obtain a connection to the IndexServer that sends the event.

        This mandatory method returns information about the application that implements the interface. It should return the application name and version and the implementors name. The returned String is printed into the log file and is added to error messages. This method is mandatory.
